search::searchStringToArray()

Description
    private array search::searchStringToArray(string $searchStr)
    Converts a string value to an array.

Parameters
    searchStr
	The string to be evaluated.

Return Values
    An array value generated from the input string.
    
Examples
    <?php
	...
	$searchString = isset($this->engine->cleanPost['MYSQL']['searchString'])?$this->engine->cleanPost['MYSQL']['searchString']:array();
	    for($i = 0; $i < $this->searchRows; $i++) {
		// convert string from text field into array
		$tmpArray = $this->searchStringToArray($searchString[$i]);
		foreach ($tmpArray as $key => $value) {
		    $output[$type][] = $value;
	        }
	    }
	...
    ?>
